doc.after: Jakarta is home to a number of universities, of which the University of Indonesia is the largest. It is a public institution with campuses in Salemba (central Jakarta) and in Depok to the south of Jakarta.[113] Aside from the University of Indonesia, the three other public universities in Jakarta are: Syarif Hidayatullah State Islamic University Jakarta, the State University of Jakarta (UNJ) and the University of Pembangunan Nasional "Veteran" Jakarta (UPN "Veteran" Jakarta). Some major private universities in Jakarta are: Trisakti University, Pancasila University, Tarumanagara University, Atma Jaya University, Pelita Harapan University and Bina Nusantara University.
